&nbsp;In Spanish, English, Spanglish and Kichwa. Carlita like you have never seen or heard her! In this show, Carlita Shaw takes you on a journey to meet Pascual Kunchicuy, a Shiwiar Warrior for the Rainforest of Ecuador and Director of IKIAM. Pascual talks with Carlita about the work he has done with the Shiwar people where he was born deep in the Ecuadorian Rainforest. Carlita and Pascual talk about what work they can do together to continue to preserve the biodiversity of the rainforest and Pascual talks about how he worked to preserve the knowledge and culture of the Shiwiar people to the Ecuadorian government through his books to preserve the Shiwiar language and mapping the Shiwiar territory, before Pascual's work, no-one new of the Shiwiar people or their plight to protect their land from the oil exploitation. Carlita and Pascual explore ways to preserve the Shiwiar territory. The interview about Pascual and the Shiwiar territory&nbsp; is followed 1 hour into the show by a very special audio guided tour by Pascual and Patricio Gualingua, a Shaman&nbsp; whom comes from an ancient family of Medicine Men. Hear an authentic audio version of our journey into the Ecuadorian Virgin Amazon Rainforest and learn about Rainforest Plant Medicine, understand how precious the Rainforest is and how you can help the Shiwiar people and Volunteer in the Amazon Rainforest.&nbsp; Pascual Kunchicuy is raising funds for to obtain a private plane for the Shiwiar people because he has had to rely on private planes to get to the settlement where the Shiwiar settlements are, it costs 1,500 dollars to hire a private plane for 6 people and ofcourse he cannot afford to pay for that to get to his people from Puyo, the Shiwiar people need a small plane for emergencies and for ongoing conservation of their territory and the volunteer projects. To make a donation to Pascual and the Shiwiar people to help them raise funds for their Wings of Hope Plane go to IKIAM DONATIONS &nbsp; Websites: Pa